  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Automation Software Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>General:</strong><br />AAT (Applied Angstrom Technology) is a start-up semiconductor equipment company with headquarter in Singapore, looking for experienced and versatile Software Engineers in Singapore. This person will play a main role in developing the automation systems for new semiconductor manufacturing equipment (FEOL). At this role, you will partner with other hardware engineer/electrical engineer/system control engineer in system validation.<br /><br /><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><p>The ideal candidate shall be able to perform the following:</p><ul><li>Develop automation/machine controlling system for our process equipment, good command of PLC programming, C/C++/C# programming is required. Knowing Python is a plus.</li><li>Troubleshoot on any system controlling or automation issues.</li><li>A broad knowledge of sensors, actuators and gas valves and communications involved is a plus.</li><li>Cooperate with other engineers to complete equipment automation and integrate hardware with software where users can control the equipment.</li><li>Service, training, troubleshooting on customer sites if any.</li><li>Assists with product presentations and sales efforts as needed.</li></ul><p><strong>Job Qualifications:</strong></p><ul><li>BS/CS is minimum, Master is preferred.</li><li>At least 5 years of motion controlling/automation application and system integration.</li><li>Knowledge in Industrial Standards, Safety Standard is required.</li><li>Knowledge of SECS/GEM is required.</li><li>Experience in the semiconductor industry is required, FEOL is preferred.</li><li>Ability to navigate a dynamic and at times ambiguous environment that requires frequent multitasking, prioritization, and a proactive mentality.</li><li>Excellent verbal and written communication skills and the ability to interact professionally with a diverse group of internal partners, team members, and suppliers.</li><li>Self-starting individual, with ability to take initiative and work independently.</li><li>Proven relationship management skills, including navigating the organization and influencing decisions.</li></ul>",
